Satureja montana

   [9584.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Lamiales:Labiatae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 9584

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is an evergreen shrub. It grows about 30-60 cm in
   height and has stiff, narrow green leaves and small white to lilac
   flowers that attract bees.GROWING PERIOD: Perennial, may be harvested
   first year and can be harvested twice in subsequent years, if plants
   are grown as perennials. USE: It grows in a spreading fashion but is
   easily pruned for use in borders and knot gardens. Winter savory adds a
   spicy taste to fish, poultry, salads, beans, vegetables, soups and
   stews. COMMON NAMES: Winter savory. FURTHER INF: It is native of the
   Mediterranean region. It will grow best in full sun and well drained
   soil.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Prakash V 1990 pp 93 [USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 407 [USE]
   Duke J 1979 pp 107 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 26 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Hornok L 1992 pp 219 [USE]

